Early Apprenticeship programs
	1. Artisans in 1700 had to train their own workers
		The training was good but not enough to make them independent
		Only a few could, and out of them only a few could afford the tools
		
	2. Guild schools
		Developed by the master craftsmen, they congregated and called themselves "yeoman".
		
	3. Yeomanries
		The first instance of labour unions came from the idea of Yeomanries, 
		when the workers were working.
		
